Do parametrized tests give me what I&#39;m looking for?

Essentially, I need to dynamically gather all classes that implement an interface, extend a base class, or are marked with an annotation and then perform contract tests on them.  I need to know:

* If any implementation is not compliant
* Exactly which ones are not compliant

I do not want to do the base class approach to creating the contract tests because people get lazy and it is extra work that doesn&#39;t necessarily have to be done.


